# Privacy Policy

**Last updated:** January 2026

## Introduction

RedTree ("we", "our", or "the app") is committed to protecting your privacy.
This Privacy Policy explains how information is collected, used, and handled
when you use the RedTree mobile application.

By using the app, you agree to the practices described in this policy.

---

## Information We Collect

### Camera Access

The RedTree app may request access to your device’s camera.

**Why we use the camera:**
- To allow users to capture photos within the app
- To support app features that require image input (such as profile images or content uploads)

We **do not** access the camera without your explicit permission.

---

## How We Use Information

- Images captured using the camera are used **only for app functionality**
- We do **not** sell, rent, or share camera data with third parties
- We do **not** use camera data for advertising or tracking

---

## Data Storage & Security

- Images are handled securely within the app
- We take reasonable measures to protect user data from unauthorized access
- Data is retained only as long as necessary for app functionality

---

## Third-Party Services

RedTree may use trusted third-party services (such as cloud infrastructure)
to operate the app. These services are required to follow appropriate
data protection practices.

We do **not** share personal data for marketing purposes.

---

## User Control

- You can deny or revoke camera permission at any time through your device settings
- Some features may not work correctly if camera access is disabled

---

## Children’s Privacy

RedTree is not intended for children under the age of 13.
We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

---

## Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time.
Any changes will be reflected on this page with an updated date.

---

## Contact Us

If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, you can contact us at:

**Email:** support@redtree.app
